1
00:00:05,055 --> 00:00:09,380
Without controlled senses
there’s no question of spontaneous love.

2
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:12,546
[Lust vs. Love]

3
00:00:12,546 --> 00:00:15,955
If someone’s senses, 
dhīra …

4
00:00:15,955 --> 00:00:16,993
There’s a śloka that says,

5
00:00:16,993 --> 00:00:23,086
vikrīḍitaṁ vraja-vadhūbhir idaṁ ca viṣṇoḥ
śraddhānvito ’nuśṛṇuyād atha varṇayed yaḥ

6
00:00:23,086 --> 00:00:35,200
bhaktiṁ parāṁ bhagavati pratilabhya kāmaṁ 
hṛd-rogam āśv apahinoty achireṇa dhīraḥ
[SB: 10.33.39]

7
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:41,987
So hṛd-rogam means ‘heart-disease’,
expressed in uncontrolled senses.

8
00:00:41,998 --> 00:00:47,978
So, without the senses
being relatively controlled

9
00:00:47,978 --> 00:00:52,904
that one is going 
to express rāga-bhakti,

10
00:00:52,904 --> 00:00:58,034
that means ‘spontaneous love’,
here; ‘rāga-mārg’.

11
00:00:58,034 --> 00:01:01,303
Now we’re back to
Saraswatī Ṭhākur’s cautions, saying,

12
00:01:01,303 --> 00:01:04,582
“If this is not there 
at the basis,

13
00:01:04,582 --> 00:01:09,050
then they may be telling
that it’s spontaneous love,

14
00:01:09,050 --> 00:01:14,165
but it is mundane, because
the senses are not controlled.”

15
00:01:14,165 --> 00:01:17,188
So they’re taking 
divine things

16
00:01:17,188 --> 00:01:20,558
and making them,
in his words, ‘vulture food’,

17
00:01:20,558 --> 00:01:23,681
saying the senses 
are like vultures.

18
00:01:23,681 --> 00:01:32,866
So, if the senses 
are under the control of lust,

19
00:01:32,989 --> 00:01:36,619
then there’s no question
of expressing spontaneous love,

20
00:01:36,619 --> 00:01:41,068
which means here 
‘rāga-bhakti’, ‘rāga-mārg’.

21
00:01:41,068 --> 00:01:42,743
So, there’s viddhi-mārg;

22
00:01:42,743 --> 00:01:49,163
they have to gradually 
come under control.

23
00:01:49,163 --> 00:01:51,318
Then, from that position, 
dhīra; 
 

24
00:01:51,318 --> 00:01:54,318
undisturbed, 
no sense disturbance,

25
00:01:54,318 --> 00:01:57,390
Then, when they hear 
the divine pastimes
 

26
00:01:57,390 --> 00:02:01,030
of Rādhārāṇī, Kṛṣṇa, 
and Vraja-gopīs,

27
00:02:01,030 --> 00:02:08,466
that will awaken spontaneous
loving sentiments within them.

28
00:02:09,835 --> 00:02:16,167
Otherwise we’ll project that our
experience of mundane love,

29
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:20,766
we’ll project that as being …

30
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:26,839
we’ll impose that idea 
on spontaneous love of rāga-bhaktas,

31
00:02:26,839 --> 00:02:29,899
and that’s an offense 
against divinity—
 

32
00:02:29,899 --> 00:02:32,899
to think these pastimes 
are mundane,

33
00:02:32,899 --> 00:02:35,537
like the mundane affairs
between men and women.

